# {{ project.name }}

A stack for [dexa.js](https://github.com/kaizendorks/dexa#readme).

## Usage
```
# publish to a git repo, for example [github](https://docs.github.com/en/github/importing-your-projects-to-github/importing-source-code-to-github/adding-an-existing-project-to-github-using-the-command-line)
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-user/{{ project.name }}
git push -u origin main

# Now anyone can install your stack...
dx stack add {{ project.name }} https://github.com/your-user/{{ project.name }}

# ...and create projects using your stack
dx init {{ project.name }}
```

## Development
```
# Install the stack from the local folder. (Run the command at the root of this repo)
dx stack add {{ project.name }} $(pwd)

# now you can test your stack by generating a project
dx init {{ project.name }} test-project

# you can clean it up with
dx stack delete {{ project.name }}
```